\begin{center}
\section{ \Large  METHODOLOGY}
\end{center}

\\\\
\begin{large}
\textbf{4.1 System Modules}
\end{large}
\\\\
\textbf{4.1.1 Sensor Module }\\\\
 \tab The Dirt Defender Ceiling Fan system integrates advanced dust detection sensors that function akin to human eyes, perceiving and assessing dust accumulation on fan blades. These specialized sensors are strategically mounted on the fan blades, ensuring accurate and timely detection of dust and debris. The sensors operate autonomously, continuously monitoring the fan blades' cleanliness status. Once a significant amount of dust is detected, the sensors promptly send a signal to the system's control unit, triggering the cleaning process.
 \\
 \begin{itemize}
        \item Dust Detection Sensors (LDR Sensor): These sensors are crucial components of the cleaning system, as they detect the accumulation of dust on fan blades. They are typically mounted on the fan blades themselves to ensure accurate and timely detection.
        \item Edge Detection Sensors (IR Sensor): The Infrared (IR) sensor is a pivotal component in our IoT-enabled cleaning system, serving as an
        essential tool for detecting obstacles and edges during the cleaning process. This sensor emits and
        receives infrared radiation, enabling the system to accurately identify objects in its path and adjust its
        cleaning trajectory accordingly.\\
        
\end{itemize}
    
\textbf{4.1.2 Communication Protocols }\\\\
\tab To facilitate seamless data transmission from the sensors to the control unit and the dedicated mobile app, the system employs robust communication protocols. These protocols ensure reliable and real-time communication, allowing users to stay informed about the fan's cleaning status and take prompt action when needed. The integration of these communication protocols enhances the system's responsiveness and user experience.

 \\
 \begin{itemize}
        \item Communication Protocols: The Telegram Bot API utilizes HTTPS Protocol, as shown in figure 4.1.2. via the WiFiClientSecure library in our Arduino code, ensuring a secure and encrypted communication channel between our device and the Telegram servers. This allows our Arduino-based application to send and receive messages to and from Telegram users or groups securely over the internet.
        
    \end{itemize}
    \begin{figure}[htb]
    \begin{center}
    \includegraphics[width=300pt,height=150pt]{https.png}
    \end{center}
    \
    \begin{center}
    \renewcommand{\thefigure}{4.1.2}
    \caption{\footnotesize  HTTPS Protocol}
    \end{center}
    \end{figure}
\\
\textbf{4.1.3 Cleaning Mechanism }\\\\
\tab The cleaning mechanism of the Dirt Defender Ceiling Fan system is designed for optimal efficiency and effectiveness. It features mechanical components such as duster strategically positioned to clean the fan blades thoroughly. When activated, these components move along the fan blades, gently removing dust and debris without causing any damage. The cleaning process is orchestrated by a motor control system, which regulates the movement and speed of the cleaning components, ensuring comprehensive cleaning coverage.
 \\


 \textbf{4.1.4 Dust Collection Mechanism}\\\\
 \tab An innovative feature of the Dirt Defender Ceiling Fan system is its integrated dust collection mechanism. As the cleaning components remove dust from the fan blades, the collected dust is efficiently stored in a designated container within the system. This container is designed for easy removal and disposal of the accumulated dust. Users have the flexibility to release the collected dust at their discretion, eliminating the need for manual cleaning and simplifying maintenance tasks.
 \\\\
\textbf{4.1.5 Telegram bot Module }\\\\
 \tab In addition to the dedicated Android mobile app, the system offers integration with popular messaging platforms like Telegram. The Telegram bot module acts as an interface, allowing users to remotely monitor the fan's cleaning status and initiate cleaning processes using simple commands. This integration enhances accessibility and user-friendliness, providing a familiar platform for users to interact with the system effortlessly. By using wifiClientServer library.

 
Overall, the Dirt Defender Ceiling Fan system revolutionizes ceiling fan maintenance by combining advanced sensors, intelligent cleaning mechanisms, and user-friendly interfaces. \\\\\

\textbf{4.1.6 Algorithm }\\\\
 \tab The algorithm outlines the sequence of steps followed by the cleaning system to detect dust accumulation and initiate cleaning actions. Here's a detailed breakdown of each step:
 \\
 \begin{itemize}
 \item Step 1 - Initialization of Sensor, Motors, and IoT:
 \newline Upon system startup, the sensor module, motor control system, and IoT (Internet of Things) connectivity are initialized. This includes calibration of sensors, motor positioning, and establishing communication channels.
\item  Step 2 – Checking if Sensor Gets Triggered:
\newline The system continuously monitors the dust detection sensors to check if they are triggered by the presence of dust on the fan blades. This real-time monitoring ensures prompt responsiveness to dust accumulation.

 \item Step 3 – Update Servo Motor Position:
 \newline If the sensors detect dust, the system updates the position of the servo motors. Servo motors are used to control the movement of cleaning components, such as brushes or wipers, ensuring they are directed towards the areas with dust accumulation.

\item Step 4 – Direct Sensor Trigger Moves Cleaning Robot:
\newline If a sensor is directly triggered by dust accumulation in a specific direction, the cleaning robot is moved in that direction. This targeted approach optimizes cleaning efficiency by focusing on areas with higher dust concentrations.
 \item Step 5 – Stop:
 \newline Once the cleaning robot has completed its cleaning cycle or if no further dust accumulation is detected, the system stops the cleaning process. This helps conserve energy and ensures that the cleaning robot operates only when necessary.
 \end{itemize}
 
By following this algorithm and leveraging the functionalities of each system module, the dust cleaning robot can effectively detect and remove dust from fan blades, providing improved air quality and system performance. The integration of the Telegram bot module further enhances user convenience and system accessibility, making it easier for users to monitor and control the cleaning process remotely.




